  <brief_title>Phase 1 Trial of Hu5F9-G4, a CD47-targeting Antibody</brief_title>
  <official_title>A First-in-Human Phase 1 Dose Escalation Trial of Hu5F9-G4 in Patients With Advanced Solid Malignancies</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Forty Seven, Inc.</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Forty Seven, Inc.</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to assess the safety and tolerability of Hu5F9-G4 in
      participants with solid tumors.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This is a first-in-human, first-in-class, escalating dose trial of an antibody that inhibits
      an anti-apoptotic signal in human macrophages. The major aims of the study are to define the
      safety profile of this new drug, and to determine a recommended dose and schedule for
      potential additional trials.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
